line_1: That Basket did these dying Fingers weave:
line_2: My boxen Flute to Corydon I leave,

line_1: At noon in the shade help her chaplets to weave,
line_2: She rambles about, and I meet her at eve;

line_1: But scarce I seek the airy threads to weave,
To this the wreath I weave.
Chaplets for thee our sons shall weave,
"Learn of the Mole to plow, the Worm to weave;
line_2: "Thy Arts of building from the Bee receive;

line_1: Then fix the Loom, their Fingers nimbly weave,
line_2: And thus their Toil prophetick Songs deceive.

line_1: A Posy for grim PLUTO weave,
line_2: And in smooth numbers ask his leave.

line_1: Went out, her 'custom'd bower to weave,
YE fair, for whom the hands of Hymen weave
line_2: While pleasing pains the conscious bosom heave,

line_1: But take up my shuttle and weave:
line_2: Such clowns have no art to deceive.

line_1: Should round our hearth fantastic measures weave,
line_2: The wood-land nymphs, and gentle fays, at eve
One other vision give me leave,

line_1: Blush'd not religion's olive branch to weave.
line_2: In elder time thus heroes wont t' atchieve
